  "text": "The study includes all starting runners of Gothenburg's half-marathon during 5 years, 2013-2017. The half-marathon has been in operation for 35 years and is the largest half-marathon race in the world, with around 62,000 entries every year. The race is staged annually in the central parts of Gothenburg, the second largest city of Sweden, in the middle of May [CITATION_1] . In total, 230,501 starting runners took part in the race during the 5 years, thereby comprising the study population.",
  "correct_citation": {
